On Sat, 27 Dec 2025 at 11:14, Wendy Loockx <wendy@abracasabra.es> wrote:
Hello,

Sorry for the delay in answering the questions.
Herewith some more information I have received:

- Attached the plano parcela now submitted to land registry
- The timing is estimated at around 3 months but obviously that is dependent on land registry but all 3 owners are using the same lawyer to simplify the process and everyone is in agreement of boundary
- There is no town water or community supply in the area. They have never explored having a well
- The property is listed at 2 bedroom with potential to reconfigure to create a 3 or 4 bed
- The timescale i will explain they are south african citizens and their passports expired. Unfortunately they planned to go to madrid to initiate the renewal but the lady fell and broke her hip. She is 86 so this has seriously reduced are mobility. They have made a new appointment for madrid at the end of January. However the typical return rate of a successful SA passport renewal is min 4 months. The timeframe is uncertain due to this factor and until they recieved thier passports they could not commit to any actual date. Once they have passports they will then begin the process of packing and moving
- A video tour i can do when i am next at the property although i do not have any dates in the diary as yet. I am sure soon after new year i can arrange to do this

Best regards,

Wendy

On Tue, 23 Dec 2025 at 16:46, M Mayes <m7mayes7@gmail.com> wrote:
Hi Wendy,

Thanks again for answering all of our questions, and sending over the LPO documentation and the plans - that‚Äôs really helpful!

We‚Äôve been looking through everything and just had a some follow-up questions to clarify a few of points:

Land / boundaries
You mentioned the topographic survey from September and that the corrected plot size is 17,000 m¬≤, with the neighbour‚Äôs house and pool being separated out at Land Registry and Catastro.
- Would it be possible to have a copy of the topographic plan showing the updated boundaries?
- Do you know the status and approximate timing for the regularisation at Registro and Catastro, so that the new situation is fully inscribed before a sale?

Water supply
- Do you know if any of the neighbouring properties on that part of El Hacho have mains, a community supply or registered wells, or are they all using delivered water as well?
We notice that most of them have pools so thought it could perhaps be a possibility.

Bedrooms in the listing
The listing on both your website and on Idealista states that the property has 4 bedrooms. On the plan you sent and the photos, we can clearly see only 2 bedrooms.
- Could you please clarify the number of bedrooms in case we're missing something?
This is just so we are clear in our own notes and for the bank if we decide to move forward. Looking at the floor plan, we think it could be possible to reconfigure the space to create 1-2 additional bedrooms, but this would be a lot of work.

Timing
We understand the owners cannot vacate until mid 2026 as they are returning to South Africa. We have a mortgage pre-approved, so an earlier completion in 2026 would be preferable so that we do not have to keep renewing the approval and re-submitting paperwork. We can be flexible within reason, though, so it would be helpful to know whether the owners prefer a completion date closer to their departure, or if they would consider an earlier completion with an agreed arrangement until they leave?

Video tour
Finally, if it is possible to send us a video tour of the house and terraces, we would really appreciate it, especially to get a better feel for the internal layout and how the spaces relate to the terraces and the land. We appreciate we're obviously heading into the holidays now so it might not be possible for the next week or so. We will start planning our next visit to the area in the meantime and can let you know when we can book a viewing.

Thanks again for all your help so far, and we look forward to hearing from you.

Mat & Laura

log_notes.author: Christian De Schrijver - AbraCasaBra Real Estate
log_notes.body:
@Wendy Loockx Het bericht was hier blijkbaar niet goed doorgekomen. Dit was zijn bericht. Het ging over dit pand:
https://abracasabra-realestate.com/en/property/R5140858_villa-alora/

Hi there.

My partner and I live in Formentera but we're looking to buy a house in the √Ålora/Pizarra area. We were in the area for viewings in November and we're planning a second round of viewings early in the new year.

This property interests us for a number of reasons, primarily the unique location amongst the rocks and boulders of El Hacho, but also the easy access, size, views and potential for a small glamping-type operation on the land.

It's fantastic that the house has an LPO, but could you please clarify a few other aspects?

1. Would it be possible to get a video tour of the property? In particular we're interested in the flow of the property and how the two apartments are situated (we would likely want to open it up into one larger home). A floor plan would also be great.

2. What is the situation with water?

3. You mention electricity in the listing - is this mains?

4. The catastro and registro both show that this property has a parcela of 37,000m2, and that there's a second 60m2 vivienda and 40m2 pool, but the listing only mentions 15,000m2 and doesn't mention a separate house or pool. Could you please clear up the discrepancy? https://www1.sedecatastro.gob.es/Cartografia/mapa.aspx?del=29&mun=12&refcat=29012A033000350000UL&final=&ZV=NO&anyoZV=

5. Leading on from question 4 - if the current parcela is segregated, please can you provide the proposed boundary plan and status/timeline for the segregation.

6. Could you share the nota simple, and a copy of the LPO/LFO documentation?

7. Has the owner ever applied for (or enquired about) a pool licence, additional accommodation, or a rural tourism licence? If so, what was the outcome?

8. What type of septic tank does the property have, and is it documented/updated?

9. What is the annual IBI?

10. Could you clarify the land classification(s)? Looking at the √Ålora PGOU it looks like it's SNU then the southern half becomes NUP-S1, which is likely protected. This could potentially rule out even a small glamping setup.

Many questions! But they're just the questions we would ask during the viewing anyway, so it saves time to ask them now.

Many thanks.
Mat

Beste Leen,

Via mijn collega Nathalie kreeg ik uw berichtje door betreft een bezoek aan de villa in Cartama: abracasabra-realestate.com/en/property/R4965172/

De Villa is gelegen in een zeer fijne buurt met goede verbinding naar Malaga.
Wel dien ik te vermelden dat de overkapping die is aangezet er staat zonder vergunning. En nog niet volledig is afgewerkt, idem voor het appartement dit dient ook nog verder te worden afgewekt. De woning is niet aangesloten op water van het net, wel is er een gigantische deposit aanwezig dus aan water geen gebrek.

Indien dit voor u geen probleem vormt, plan ik graag een bezoekje in. De eigenaars werken overdag en zijn niet heel flexibel dus indien mogelijk best na 17u als dat voor u kan? Laat het me alvast weten dan doe ik navraag.

Ik heb nog een leuke woning in Alora deze staat nog niet op de markt, deze is volledig vernieuwd en heeft heel wat mogelijkheden. Ik stuur u hierbij alvast wat meer informatie omtrent deze. Indien gewenst kunnen we deze ook bezoeken.

log_notes.author: Wendy Loockx
log_notes.body:
Beste Rene,

Ik kreeg via onze website een aanvraag binnen voor volgende woning te Alora:
abracasabra-realestate.com/property/?ref_no=R5207797
Helaas zie ik verder niet meer gegevens, dus ik geef alvast graag wat meer informatie mee.
Deze woning is gelegen in de mooie en rustige bergen van Alora. De weg er naartoe is dan ook bochtig maar zeer goed bereikbaar en alles ligt in beton.
De woning zelf, heeft wat algemene opknapwerkjes nodig waaronder het zwembad en de keuken en vooral buiten de muur rond het pand. Maar gezien het beschikt over 3 slaapkamer aan een mooie prijs voor deze regio is dit op zich wel een buitenkans om er een klein paradijsje van te maken.

Mocht u graag meer informatie wensen, of een bezoek inplannen verneem ik het graag.

Met vriendelijke groet,
